      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const vacancy = $input.first().json;\n\nconst prompt = `Analyze this job vacancy and generate a SHORT optimized LinkedIn search query.\n\nVacancy title: ${vacancy.title}\nLocation: ${vacancy.location}\nDescription: ${vacancy.description_clean}\n\nRules:\n- IGNORE the company description at the beginning ({{REDACTED}} boilerplate)\n- Focus ONLY on the \"What It Takes To Succeed\" and \"What You'll Do\" sections\n- Extract the specific technologies, tools and experience level mentioned\n- Return a SHORT LinkedIn search query (max 6 words)\n- Include seniority level if mentioned (senior, manager, etc)\n- Do NOT include location\n- Return ONE search phrase, not a comma-separated list\n\nExamples of good output:\n- \"Senior Backend Developer .NET C# MySQL\"\n- \"Business Development Manager media adtech\"\n- \"Data Science Manager Python machine learning\"\n\nReturn ONLY raw JSON no markdown:\n{\"optimized_keywords\": \"...\", \"seniority\": \"junior|mid|senior|manager\", \"key_skills\": [\"skill1\", \"skill2\", \"skill3\"]}`;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...vacancy,\n    claude_body: {\n      model: \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n      max_tokens: 500,\n      messages: [{ role: \"user\", content: prompt }]\n    }\n  }\n}];"
      },
